# Header action hierarchy

Each header row (app shell, `.z-mail-text-nav__row`, settings nav bar) may have **at most one strong action**.

## Strong vs secondary

| Role | Class / pattern | Weight |
|------|-----------------|--------|
| **Strong action** (max 1) | `.z-mail-text-nav__action` or one primary `Button` in app shell | semibold |
| Secondary actions | `.z-mail-text-nav__link` | normal |
| Destructive secondary | `.z-mail-text-nav__link--danger` | normal |
| Overflow / More / Actions | `textTrigger` + `.z-mail-text-nav__link` | normal |
| Title / folder name | `.z-mail-text-nav__title` | normal — never bold |
| Brand / logo | plain text in shell — **not** `.z-type-brand` | normal |

## Layout pattern

```
[ secondary links … ]     [ title — normal weight ]     [ optional __action ]
```

Examples:
- **Inbox list**: Settings (link) · **New message** (action)
- **Reader**: Back · Done (link) · **Reply** (action) · More (link)
- **Compose**: Close · Discard (link) · **Send** (action)
- **Bulk bar**: Cancel (link) · summary (normal) · Trash (link--danger) · Actions (link)

## Do not

- Put `font-semibold` / `font-bold` on titles, logos, or summary text in headers
- Use `.z-type-brand` in app shell or text-nav titles (reserve for auth/marketing pages)
- Style overflow triggers with `.z-mail-text-nav__action`
- Add a second strong action (e.g. Trash button + Actions both semibold)

## When adding a header

1. Pick the single primary outcome → `__action`
2. Demote everything else → `__link` (or `__link--danger` for delete)
3. Keep the title/logo at normal weight
